I looked into this and it seems that we need to update from .NET Core 3.1 to .NET 6 first as we're affected by this issue: dotnet/runtime#61602.
I'll add a note in TINKERPOP-2651 where we update to .NET 6 that we can afterwards also do this update.

@dependabot ignore this major version

@spmallette I don't know enough about the topic but I was wondering wether JDK 9 modules would allow to eliminate conflicts between libraries java runtime versions?
https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_Platform_Module_System
Anyway thanks again for your contributions :)

@divijvaidya thanks for the feedback!

I responded to a majority of your comments to keep track of what we have already tackled in milestone 2 as well as additional changes that were made to address your points.

Anything that wasn't addressed is tracked and will either require work at a later time, or some investigation on what the best way to approach finding a solution is.
